title: Search for missing nine-year-old girl north of Brisbane intensifies - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
Search for missing nine-year-old girl north of Brisbane intensifies Posted February 19, 2017 15:33:35 Map: Caboolture 4510 
Queensland police have issued an Amber Alert, asking for help from the public to find a missing nine-year-old girl who has not been seen since this morning at Bellmere. 
The girl is described as Caucasian in appearance, of a slim build, with an olive complexion and blonde shoulder-length hair. 
She was wearing a one-piece black and pink swimming costume with a butterfly on it when she was last seen at Seville Street about 9:30am. 
Police and family have concerns for her welfare due to her age and because she has a medical condition. 
People in the Bellmere area have been urged to check their yards and surroundings for her.
